4.00	Chapelle_Show	Chappelle's Show	Chappelle's Show is an American sketch comedy television series created by comedian Dave Chappelle and Neal Brennan, with Chappelle hosting the show as well as starring in various skits. Chappelle, Brennan and Michele Armour were the show's executive producers. The series premiered on January 22, 2003 on the American cable television network Comedy Central. The show ran for two complete seasons and a third, truncated season (dubbed "The Lost Episodes").	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/5/5b/Chappelle_logo.jpg/250px-Chappelle_logo.jpg
